			<pubDate>Tue, 01 Jul 2008 06:21:15 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I just got back from seeing Wanted, but this thread isn't about Wanted, it's about the theatre!

The Galaxy theatre in Gig Harbor, about 10 minutes from where I live has a "VIP Theatre", which is, perhaps, the most brilliant idea for a movie venue ever. You pay a bit more for the ticket, but you...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I just got back from seeing Wanted, but this thread isn't about Wanted, it's about the theatre!<br />
<br />
The Galaxy theatre in Gig Harbor, about 10 minutes from where I live has a &quot;VIP Theatre&quot;, which is, perhaps, the most brilliant idea for a movie venue ever. You pay a bit more for the ticket, but you also get bigger seats, more room between the seats with a place to put your drink, candy, etc... and you can order drinks during the film. Pay for it in advance, tell them to bring you a new beer every 15 minutes, and they'll keep them coming.<br />
<br />
This is like first class moviegoing, in exactly the same way you'd think of first class flying. And it's awesome. Top it off, and Galaxy theatres in this area are all brand new, with beautiful Cristie digital projectors, and you've got a top notch movie experience that beats going to a bar by a mile. From this day forward, I don't think I'll ever go to a &quot;normal&quot; movie again.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
