			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>It's been what, a week? Two? I can't remember the last time I saw a blue sky, because for the past week or so California has been <br />
<b><i><u><font size="7"><font color="Red">ON FIRE</font></font></u></i></b><br />
<br />
The best part is, I'm so cut off from the real world in college town, what with no active classes and no cable connection, nor really any desire to browse sites other than graffe's and gaming sites, that I didn't even realize California was<br />
<b><i><u><font size="7"><font color="Red">ON FIRE</font></font></u></i></b><br />
until a few days ago. I just thought the marine layer in SLO had come in and stayed put. Does that some times.<br />
<br />
So I drove home on Friday and I pop over the hills into the San Joaquin valley, and I'm looking at a sky that looks like China-Lite. &quot;WTF?!&quot; I say to myself. That's no cloud.<br />
<br />
Anyway, the air is cleaning out here. Maybe the throbbing headaches I've had for the past 6 days will stop. Between this and grindel's recent wind issues, all that's left is the great quake, and we're looking at armageddon. Are you prepared?<br />
<br />
Oh. And just because I like the way it looks: California, it's still pretty much<br />
<b><i><u><font size="7"><font color="Red">ON FIRE</font></font></u></i></b></div>

